## 📋 Test Report: Triple-Click Selection Behavior in Slate Angular Editor

### ✅ Editor Found & Void Elements Identified

**Location:** `http://localhost:8000/inlines`

**Paragraph with Void Element:**
> *"In addition to block nodes, you can create inline nodes. Here is a **hyperlink**, and here is a more unusual inline: an **[editable button]** !"*

This paragraph contains:
- Regular text
- A **hyperlink** (inline node)
- An **`[editable button]`** — an **inline void element** (rendered as a bordered button widget embedded within the text flow)
- Text "!" after the void element

---

### 🔴 BUG FOUND: Triple-Click Does NOT Select Entire Paragraph

**Expected Behavior:**  
In a standard rich text editor (like Slate.js), triple-clicking on text within a paragraph should select **the entire paragraph block**, including all inline content — text, hyperlinks, and inline void elements like `[editable button]`.

**Actual Behavior:**  
Triple-clicking selects **only the single word** at the cursor position. Multiple tests confirmed this consistently:

| Test | Click Location | Expected | Actual |
|------|---------------|----------|--------|
| 1 | Word "addition" | Entire paragraph selected | Only "addition" selected |
| 2 | Word "block" | Entire paragraph selected | Only "block" selected |
| 3 | Word "create" | Entire paragraph selected | Only "create" selected |

**The `[editable button]` inline void element is never included in the selection** when triple-clicking. The selection stops at the single word boundary, never extending to cover the paragraph's void elements.

---

### 🔴 Visual Anomaly

The `[editable button]` void element appears as a small bordered box with text inside it, embedded inline within the paragraph. While visually it looks correct (it's positioned appropriately in the text flow), the **selection behavior is broken** — triple-click should encompass it as part of a full paragraph selection, but it doesn't.

---

### ✅ Conclusion

**The entire paragraph including void elements does NOT get selected on triple-click.** This is a **functional bug** in the Slate Angular editor's triple-click selection handler. The triple-click behavior is limited to word-level selection instead of block/paragraph-level selection, which fails to include inline void elements (like `[editable button]`) or any text beyond the clicked word.
